accessibility.text: Humans are hardwired to think categorically.
Humans are hardwired to think categorically.
The most obvious reason is the importance for early man of determining whether a footprint was that of a deadly saber-tooth tiger or a potentially life-giving ancient antelope.
Humans are hardwired to think categorically.
The most obvious reason is the importance for early man of determining whether a footprint was that of a deadly saber-tooth tiger or a potentially life-giving ancient antelope.
Human intelligence specializes in pattern recognition and inductive generalization, which is “messy, inconsistent, and often quite ‘illogical’ in a strictly deductive sense.”
